1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 509 of Title 69, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
5 fund for the Oklahoma Department of Transportation to be designated
6 as the "Major Collector Routes Fund". The fund shall be a
7 continuing fund not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
8 consist of all monies received by the Department from
9 appropriations. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are
10 hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
11 Department for purposes of this act. Expenditures of said fund
12 shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against
13 claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
14 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
15 B. The Department of Transportation shall establish a grant
16 program, and shall promulgate rules for said program for the
17 counties to apply for the funds. Projects under consideration shall
18 be evaluated and prioritized based on:
19 1. Project innovation;
20 2. Readiness;
21 3. Structured adequacy;
22 4. Safety;
23 5. Serviceability;
24 6. Functional obsolescence;
Req. No. 13439 Page 2

1 7. Essentiality for public use; and
2 8. Special reductions for characteristics such as detour
3 length, traffic safety features, and current school bus routes.
4 C. The direct or indirect financial participation by the county
5 proposing the project shall be an additional selection factor for
6 proposed projects, along with the objective distribution of funding.
7 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
8 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
